naomi kotake retires from the eal sulair sulair home searchworks e journals databases off campus access ask us sulair news logo sulair news home all articles submit article search sulair news library web sites searchworks databases az socrates google books google scholar search this site sulair news about sulair news back issues get email announcements submit article user login login with your sunet id home groups sulair news naomi kotake retires from the eal after 20 years of service to stanford naomi kotake retires effective march 1 2011 since november 1990 naomi has worked full time as the japanese cataloger at first and later the japanese bibliographer in the hoover east asia collection and as japanese studies librarian in stanford east asia library when it was transferred to sulair in fall 2001 naomi brought to stanford and sulair a deep understanding of collection building and development in all fields of japanese studies and she participated actively in reaching out and expertly delivering services to students faculty and researchers she co authored library of congress subject headings related to japan topical headings 1994 in 2004 two librarians from north american were invited to attend the international symposium on northeast china and japan held in niigata japan and she had an opportunity to present a paper on stanford's rich japanese resources on manchuria in her retirement naomi looks forward to devoting more time to enjoy her hobbies certainly we all wish her the best in these activities and wish her a wonderful and fulfilling retirement by dongfang shao director of the east asia library submitted by qqiu stanford edu on tue 03 01 2011 12 43 back stanford university stanford california 94305 650 725 1064 terms of use copyright complaints
